<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-06-22T18:26:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1954-06-22T18:26:00-05:00" n="802" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d802">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">396.1 GE/6–2154: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">United States
                                        Delegation</gloss></hi><note n="1" xml:id="d802fn1">Drafted
                                    by <persName corresp="#p_SPJ1">Sturm</persName> of <gloss target="#t_FE1">FE</gloss>/<gloss target="#t_PSA1">PSA</gloss>.</note></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret<lb/>priority</hi></seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1954-06-22T19:26:00-04:00">June 22, 1954—7:26
                                        p.m.</date></dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p><gloss target="#t_Tosec1">Tosec</gloss> 461. Proposal reported <gloss target="#t_Secto1">Secto</gloss> 496<note n="2" xml:id="d802fn2">Dated June 21, <ref target="#pg_1210">p. 1210</ref>.</note> is
                                consistent with working methods adopted by conference but as
                                indicated in <gloss target="#t_Tedul1">Tedul</gloss> 211<note n="3" xml:id="d802fn3">Dated June 17, <ref target="#pg_1171">p.
                                        1171</ref>.</note> we do not wish participate in work of
                                committees which may take decisions from which it might be awkward
                                for us later to dissociate ourselves.</p>
                            <pb facs="1248" n="1222" xml:id="pg_1222"/>
                            <p>Suggest you reiterate to <persName corresp="#p_CJ1">Chauvel</persName> that we would not be prepared accept
                                membership in any “<hi rend="italic">ad hoc</hi> commissions” which
                                in our view should be constituted only of principals.</p>
                            <closer><signed><persName corresp="#p_DJF1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Dulles</hi></persName></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>